idate hypervelocity star, the TGAS\nproper motion implying a very large peculiar transverse velocity (~360 km/s)\ndirected radially away from the LMC centre. If confirmed, for example by Gaia\nData Release 2, it would imply that this massive supergiant, on the periphery\nof the LMC, is leaving the galaxy where it will explode as a supernova.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Nov 2016 23:35:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 11 Mar 2017 17:34:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-07-19"}
